Diagnosis. Dorsal surface of body segments smooth, bearing detached fine setae ( Figs 39 , 40 ). Eyes presented ( Figs 40 , 65 ), ommatidia reduced, weakly pigmented. Vital body color is light yellowish. Head with rostral point (
Fig. 66
). Inferior antennal sinus moderate, sub-rounded (
Fig. 65
). Antenna 1 10 % longer than antenna 2 . Ventral margins of epimera 1–3 unarmed. Ventral surface of urosomite 1 bearing 2 notched robust and 4 flexible setae. Uropod 3 with a naked peduncular process. Telson as long as uropod 3 peduncle. Ventral surface of pereonites 2–7 with sternal humps. Body length 5.7 – 8.0 mm (females), 4.0 – 6.0 mm (males).
